[node name="Label" type="Label" parent="Tutorial/PanelContainer"]
layout_mode = 2
theme_override_font_sizes/font_size = 20
text = "-EMERGENCY PROTOCOL 4811: One Large Leap for Man-
You seem to have lept forward in time so much, you broke out of it. Situations like this can only be remedied by leveraging your own life into your time engine. 

To begin, press 'Calibrate' then move the slider to select how much time you are giving up. 
After confirming, the hands on the time engine will begin to move. Press 'Space' or 'E' t to stop a hand. The closer you are to the center of the indicator, the more time you will get back. 

If you get enough time, the engine will automatically move us a sector forward. Going over the amount required to move us grants you time crystals, which we can use in our fabriactor to upgrade the engine Careful, adding loads of time makes the arms spin more, and your engine seems to have a leak, so you can lose time if youre not careful

Scans show that youre 8 sectors away from getting back, keep reaching the threshold and you will return safely

Press [E] to close"
autowrap_mode = 2

